The Liaison Office of the Central People's Government in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region said Friday that it supports the anti-mask law enacted on Friday by the HKSAR government. "One country, two systems principle won't change, won't be shaken to the core, but we can't tolerate rioters seriously challenging sovereignty and damaging public security," the office said.  
